        <ontology:isPresentedBefore rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N188_VC_11_CH2/event/ev8"/>
        <ontology:is_identified_by rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/appellation/Interest_on_this_VC"/>
        <ontology:partOfNarrative rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N188_VC_11_CH2"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/phenomenal_place/47.28155796902394_7.140358538002457"/>
        <ontology:hasDescription>The cake has a strong terrirotial identitity, being considered as a traditional speciality form the Jura canton, consumed extensively during local festivals. It is produced from flour and cream, made from the abundant dairy resources in the region.  </ontology:hasDescription>
    </NamedIndividual>
    


    <!-- https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N188_VC_11_CH2/event/ev8 -->


    <NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N188_VC_11_CH2/event/ev8">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/event-type/valorisation_event"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/ontology#Event"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q10876"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q13228"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q210272"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q37828"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q8495"/>
        <ontology:isPresentedBefore rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N188_VC_11_CH2/event/ev9"/>
        <ontology:is_identified_by rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/appellation/Key_local_assets"/>
        <ontology:partOfNarrative rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N188_VC_11_CH2"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/phenomenal_place/47.28155796902394_7.140358538002457"/>
        <ontology:hasDescription>Before refrigerators, the acidification of cream was done without human intervention. The raw milk was stored in a cool place for several days. The cream would rise to the surface and, as it aged, acquire a sour taste through bacterial transformation. The recipe has maintained this old artisanal production technique which is a strong cultural asset.   </ontology:hasDescription>
    </NamedIndividual>
    


